GOLD CROWN MINING COMPANY, Limited, v. BYRON JACKSON COMPANY. No. 9928. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Sept. 29, 1941. Lester V. Peterman, of Twenty Nine Palms, Cal., for appellant. Latham & Watkins and Henry T. Moore, all of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, GARRECHT, and DENMAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On stipulation of counsel for respective parties and good cause therefor appearing, ordered appeal herein dismissed, that a decree be filed and entered accordingly, and that the mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
